morgan guidance services is a psychologists & counseling services provider based in florida, united states.
long_description: our team is your team. as a parent and a professional working with young people and families for almost 40 years, elaine has always been deeply passionate about special education and family life education. elaine's sub specialties include students and adults who are off track in some way when compared with same age peers: adhd, high functioning asperger, asd, learning challenges, emotional immaturity, failure to launch and a wide variety of challenging behaviors. she has advanced training in forensic interviewing, cognitive coaching and neuropsychological assessment, as well as special interests and study in neurodiversity, pathological demand avoidance, trauma, attachment and relational neurobiology. we align with ethical organizations and value collegiality with other professionals in our fields. we integrate services with a developmental perspective so caregivers, students and entire families can regulate, feel safe, heal and reach potential in life. we enjoy sharing our personal journey and expertise within communities and beyond.

generated_description: morgan guidance, legally known as morgan guidance services llc., based in orlando, florida, is a company specializing in providing guidance and support for families with special needs. founded by elaine morgan, ed.m., the company offers a range of services including parent coaching, therapeutic placement, educational planning, and career counseling. morgan guidance services focuses on addressing issues such as adhd, high-functioning autism, schizophrenia, depression, anxiety, and learning difficulties. the company serves families across the united states, including regions such as florida, texas, and the caribbean. elaine morgan, with nearly 40 years of experience in special education and family life education, leads the team, bringing a unique perspective and extensive background in education, social services, and career counseling.
